-- 
Six People Killed in House Fire in London, Authorities Say

-- B y   M i k e   H a r r i s o n
-- 
2011-09-24T08:32:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/six-people-killed-in-house-fire-in-london-authorities-say-1-.html
Six people, including five
children, have died in a house fire in north west London today.  Two other people who escaped before firefighters arrived
were injured and have been taken to hospital, London Fire
Brigade said in an e-mailed statement.  All those killed and injured are believed to be members of
the same family, the Metropolitan Police said.  “Police have launched an investigation following a fire in
Neasden,” the Met said in an e-mailed statement.  The police said the victims were a 41-year-old woman, three
girls aged 14, 13 and nine and two boys aged five and two.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  